Script Reference

1. Introduction

CloakBone2D is a Unity C# script designed to animate cloak or robe bones in 2D games.
It simulates natural fabric movement both when the character is idle and when moving.

Idle: the cloak gently sways as if moved by wind.

Moving: the cloak bends backward with turbulence, simulating air resistance.

This script provides a simple way to enhance character visuals without using physics.

2. Installation

Import the package into your Unity project.

Locate the script in your project folder: Scripts/CloakBone2D.cs.

Drag and drop the script onto your character GameObject.

3. Setup Guide

Select the GameObject with your character.

Add the CloakBone2D component if not already present.

In the Inspector, assign the Target Bone (Transform) that controls the cloak or robe.

Adjust parameters (wind, movement, turbulence) to achieve the desired effect.

Press Play and test both idle and moving states.

4. Inspector Parameters

Target Bone: The bone transform to animate.

Wind Strength: Amplitude of idle wind sway (degrees).

Wind Speed: Speed of oscillation when idle.

Move Influence: Influence of character movement on cloak angle.

Return Speed: Speed at which the cloak returns to its base rotation.

Turbulence Strength: Additional sway strength while moving.

Turbulence Speed: Frequency of turbulence oscillation.

Movement Threshold: Minimum speed for the character to be considered moving.

5. Example Use Cases

RPG or fantasy characters wearing cloaks.

Necromancer, wizard, or mage with a robe.

Enemy bosses with capes to add dynamic visuals.

Idle example: cloak sways slowly as the character stands still.
Moving example: cloak bends backward with additional flutter.

6. Limitations

Designed for 2D characters (rotation only on Z-axis).

Does not use Unity Physics2D, purely procedural.

Not intended for 3D models.

Attach this script to your character, assign a bone, and tune parameters for the desired effect.